inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getRealtimeLogConfig.

name.description: Unique name to identify this real-time log configuration.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getRealtimeLogConfig.

arn.description: ARN (Amazon Resource Name) of the CloudFront real-time log configuration.

endpoints.description: (Required) Amazon Kinesis data streams where real-time log data is sent.

fields.description: (Required) Fields that are included in each real-time log record. See the [AWS documentation](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonCloudFront/latest/DeveloperGuide/real-time-logs.html#understand-real-time-log-config-fields) for supported values.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

samplingRate.description: (Required) Sampling rate for this real-time log configuration. The sampling rate determines the percentage of viewer requests that are represented in the real-time log data. An integer between `1` and `100`, inclusive.
